The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 September is 3,208 (371.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 September, there were 118 new confirmed cases (13.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 September, there were 108 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% (10 extra cases).
